31719/// printInstruction - This method is automatically generated by tablegen
31720/// from the instruction set description.

34098#ifndef NDEBUG
34099 static struct SortCheck {
34100 SortCheck(ArrayRef<PatternsForOpcode> OpToPatterns) {
34101 assert(std::is_sorted(
34102 OpToPatterns.begin(), OpToPatterns.end(),
34103 [](const PatternsForOpcode &L, const PatternsForOpcode &R) {
34104 return L.Opcode < R.Opcode;
34105 }) &&
34106 "tablegen failed to sort opcode patterns");
34107 }
34108 } sortCheckVar(OpToPatterns);
34109#endif
34110
34111 AliasMatchingData M {
34112 makeArrayRef(OpToPatterns),
34113 makeArrayRef(Patterns),
34114 makeArrayRef(Conds),
34115 StringRef(AsmStrings, array_lengthof(AsmStrings)),
34116 &RISCVInstPrinterValidateMCOperand,
34117 };
34118 const char *AsmString = matchAliasPatterns(MI, &STI, M);
34119 if (!AsmString) return false;
34120
34121 unsigned I = 0;
34122 while (AsmString[I] != ' ' && AsmString[I] != '\t' &&
34123 AsmString[I] != '$' && AsmString[I] != '\0')
34124 ++I;
34125 OS << '\t' << StringRef(AsmString, I);
34126 if (AsmString[I] != '\0') {
34127 if (AsmString[I] == ' ' || AsmString[I] == '\t') {
34128 OS << '\t';
34129 ++I;
34130 }
34131 do {
34132 if (AsmString[I] == '$') {
34133 ++I;
34134 if (AsmString[I] == (char)0xff) {
34135 ++I;
34136 int OpIdx = AsmString[I++] - 1;
34137 int PrintMethodIdx = AsmString[I++] - 1;
34138 printCustomAliasOperand(MI, Address, OpIdx, PrintMethodIdx, STI, OS);
34139 } else
34140 printOperand(MI, unsigned(AsmString[I++]) - 1, STI, OS);
34141 } else {
34142 OS << AsmString[I++];
34143 }
34144 } while (AsmString[I] != '\0');
34145 }
34146
34147 return true;
34148}
34149
34150void RISCVInstPrinter::printCustomAliasOperand(
34151 const MCInst *MI, uint64_t Address, unsigned OpIdx,
34152 unsigned PrintMethodIdx,
34153 const MCSubtargetInfo &STI,
34154 raw_ostream &OS) {
34155 switch (PrintMethodIdx) {
34156 default:
34157 llvm_unreachable("Unknown PrintMethod kind");
34158 break;
34159 case 0:
34160 printBranchOperand(MI, Address, OpIdx, STI, OS);
34161 break;
34162 case 1:
34163 printCSRSystemRegister(MI, OpIdx, STI, OS);
34164 break;
34165 case 2:
34166 printVMaskReg(MI, OpIdx, STI, OS);
34167 break;
34168 }
34169}
34170
34171static bool RISCVInstPrinterValidateMCOperand(const MCOperand &MCOp,
34172 const MCSubtargetInfo &STI,
34173 unsigned PredicateIndex) {
34174 switch (PredicateIndex) {
34175 default:
34176 llvm_unreachable("Unknown MCOperandPredicate kind");
34177 break;
34178 case 1: {
34179
34180 int64_t Imm;
34181 if (MCOp.evaluateAsConstantImm(Imm))
34182 return isShiftedInt<12, 1>(Imm);
34183 return MCOp.isBareSymbolRef();
34184
34185 }
34186 case 2: {
34187
34188 int64_t Imm;
34189 if (MCOp.evaluateAsConstantImm(Imm))
34190 return isShiftedInt<20, 1>(Imm);
34191 return MCOp.isBareSymbolRef();
34192
34193 }
34194 case 3: {
34195
34196 int64_t Imm;
34197 if (MCOp.evaluateAsConstantImm(Imm))
34198 return isInt<12>(Imm);
34199 return MCOp.isBareSymbolRef();
34200
34201 }
34202 }
34203}
